[assistant] Fixed the serialization failure in `JavaAdapterTest`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] - The `NativeObject` delegate is still temporarily attached to the Rhino top-level scope while creating the adapter, which is required for `ClassCache`.
[assistant] - Before calling `JavaAdapter.writeAdapterObject(...)`, the test now detaches the delegate from the top-level scope:
[assistant]   - `delegee.setParentScope(null)`
[assistant]   - `delegee.setPrototype(null)`
[assistant] - The `GreetingFunction` is no longer attached to the scope/prototype chain, avoiding serialization of the global scope graph that contains non-serializable `JavaAdapter`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] This should prevent:
[assistant] 
[assistant] `java.io.NotSerializableException: net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.JavaAdapter`
[assistant] 
[assistant] while still reaching the intended `JavaAdapter.writeAdapterObject(...)` and `readAdapterObject(...)` dynamic-access call sites.
