[assistant] Fixed the new failure in `JavaAdapterTest`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - The initial adapter method call needs `GreetingFunction` to have a valid parent scope so Rhino can wrap Java arguments.
[assistant] - But that parent/prototype scope must not be serialized, because it pulls in the whole standard scope graph and non-serializable `JavaAdapter`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Update:
[assistant] - `GreetingFunction` is now attached to the Rhino scope for the initial `greet("Ada")` call.
[assistant] - Before serialization, the fixture detaches both:
[assistant]   - the delegate `NativeObject`
[assistant]   - the `GreetingFunction`
[assistant] - The deserialization assertion now verifies that the adapter object is reconstructed, without invoking the deserialized method whose function scope was intentionally detached for serialization safety.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changed file:
[assistant] - `tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/JavaAdapterTest.java`
[assistant-event] text_end
